window.onload = function() {
  var imgs = document.getElementsByTagName('img'), i, img;
  for (i = 0; i < imgs.length; i++) {
    img = imgs[i];
    // center an image if it is the only element of its parent

  }
};

<body>
<h1>Peer-graded Assignment: Course Project 1</h1>

<p>Loading and preprocessing the data</p>

<p>Reading the activity .csv file:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity &lt;- read.csv(&quot;activity.csv&quot;, header = TRUE)
</code></pre>

<p>Converting and the testing of the date format:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity$date &lt;- format(as.Date(activity$date, &quot;%m/%d/%Y&quot;), &quot;%Y-%m-%d&quot;)
str(activity$date)
</code></pre>

<pre><code>##  chr [1:17568] &quot;2012-10-01&quot; &quot;2012-10-01&quot; &quot;2012-10-01&quot; &quot;2012-10-01&quot; ...
</code></pre>

<pre><code class="r">activity$date &lt;- as.Date(activity$date)
str(activity$date)
</code></pre>

<pre><code>##  Date[1:17568], format: &quot;2012-10-01&quot; &quot;2012-10-01&quot; &quot;2012-10-01&quot; &quot;2012-10-01&quot; &quot;2012-10-01&quot; ...
</code></pre>

<p>What is mean total number of steps taken per day?</p>

<p>Creating dataframe of daily cumulative steps:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_steps_day &lt;- with(activity, aggregate(steps, by = list(date), sum))
colnames(activity_steps_day) &lt;- c(&quot;date&quot;,&quot;steps&quot;)
</code></pre>

<p>Histogram of the daily cumulative steps:</p>

<pre><code class="r">hist(activity_steps_day$steps, xlab=&quot;Daily Steps&quot;, main=&quot;Daily Steps Histogram&quot;)
</code></pre>

<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-5"/></p>

<p>Computing the daily mean of the number of steps:</p>

<pre><code class="r">mean(activity_steps_day$steps, na.rm = TRUE)
</code></pre>

<pre><code>## [1] 10766.19
</code></pre>

<p>Computing the daily median of the number of steps</p>

<pre><code class="r">median(activity_steps_day$steps, na.rm = TRUE)
</code></pre>

<pre><code>## [1] 10765
</code></pre>

<p>Setting up average number of step per interval</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_steps_interval &lt;- aggregate(steps ~ interval, activity, mean)
</code></pre>

<p>Line plot of average number of steps per 5 minute interval</p>

<pre><code class="r">plot(activity_steps_interval$interval,
     activity_steps_interval$steps, 
     type = &quot;l&quot;, 
     xlab=&quot;Time of Day&quot;, 
     ylab = &quot;Steps&quot;,
     main = &quot;Average Number of Steps&quot;)
</code></pre>

<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-9"/></p>

<p>Sorting using arrange to see the highest number of average steps:</p>

<pre><code class="r">library(dplyr)

arrange(activity_steps_interval, desc(activity_steps_interval$steps)) [1,]
</code></pre>

<pre><code>##   interval    steps
## 1      835 206.1698
</code></pre>

<p>Double checking by getting max value:</p>

<pre><code class="r">max(unlist(activity_steps_interval$steps), na.rm = TRUE)
</code></pre>

<pre><code>## [1] 206.1698
</code></pre>

<p>The value matches the value from the first output.</p>

<p>Imputing missing values</p>

<p>Counting the number of NAs:</p>

<pre><code class="r">length(activity$steps[is.na(activity$steps)])
</code></pre>

<pre><code>## [1] 2304
</code></pre>

<pre><code class="r">length(activity$date[is.na(activity$date)])
</code></pre>

<pre><code>## [1] 0
</code></pre>

<pre><code class="r">length(activity$interval[is.na(activity$interval)])
</code></pre>

<pre><code>## [1] 0
</code></pre>

<p>Because there are not any NAs in the date and interval fields, the NA count from the steps field is enough.</p>

<p>Creating the imputed data dataframe:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_impute &lt;- activity
</code></pre>

<p>Merging the imputed dataframe and the earlier average activity step interval created earlier, thus using the average by interval.</p>

<pre><code class="r">activty_merge &lt;- merge(activity_impute, activity_steps_interval, by=&quot;interval&quot;)
</code></pre>

<p>Creating a list where steps are NA:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activty_na_list &lt;- which(is.na(activity_impute$steps))
</code></pre>

<p>Replacing the NAs with the average interval values:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_impute[activty_na_list,&quot;steps&quot;] &lt;- activty_merge[activty_na_list,&quot;steps.y&quot;]
</code></pre>

<p>Imputed data frame for graph and the graph:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_imputed_steps_day &lt;- with(activity_impute, aggregate (steps, by = list(date), sum))
colnames(activity_imputed_steps_day) &lt;- c(&quot;date&quot;,&quot;steps&quot;)
hist(x=activity_imputed_steps_day$steps, xlab=&quot;Daily Steps&quot;, main=&quot;Daily Steps Histogram (Imputed)&quot;)
</code></pre>

<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-17"/>
Mean of the steps with NAs removed:</p>

<pre><code class="r">mean(activity_imputed_steps_day$steps)
</code></pre>

<pre><code>## [1] 10889.8
</code></pre>

<p>Median of the steps with NAs removed:</p>

<pre><code class="r">median(activity_imputed_steps_day$steps)
</code></pre>

<pre><code>## [1] 11015
</code></pre>

<p>Setting up week dataframe:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_week &lt;- activity
</code></pre>

<p>Adding the day of week column:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_week$day_of_week &lt;- weekdays(activity$date)
</code></pre>

<p>Adding the weekday/weekend column:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_week$weekday_weekend &lt;- ifelse(activity_week$day_of_week %in% c(&quot;Saturday&quot;,&quot;Sunday&quot;), &quot;Weekend&quot;,&quot;Weekday&quot;)
</code></pre>

<p>Opening lattice package to enable the request graph:</p>

<pre><code class="r">library(lattice)
</code></pre>

<p>Setting up the data for the graph:</p>

<pre><code class="r">activity_week_data &lt;- aggregate(steps ~ weekday_weekend + interval, activity_week, mean)
</code></pre>

<p>Plot of the data:</p>

<pre><code class="r">xyplot(steps ~ interval | activity_week_data$weekday_weekend,
       data = activity_week_data,
       type = &quot;l&quot;,
       layout = c(1,2),
       main = &quot;Average Steps per Interval by Weekend/Weekday&quot;,
       xlab = &quot;Interval&quot;,
       ylab = &quot;Averge Steps&quot;)
</code></pre>
